HEADWORD: Radication
<hw>Rad`i*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*k⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>radication</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The process of taking root, or state of being rooted; <as>as, the
<ex>radication</ex> of habits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The disposition of the roots of a
plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Radicel</ent>⟦br⟧
